Requested by SENATE COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
SENATE BILL 1557
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, line 2, after “provisions;” delete the rest
2 of the line and insert “amending ORS 33.055, 33.065, 33.075, 109.232 and
3 476.274; and prescribing an effective date.”.
4 After line 3, insert:
5
6 “CONTEMPT PROCEEDINGS”.
7
8 On page 2, delete lines 12 through 14 and insert:
9 “(c) Upon being served, the contempt defendant may, but is not required
10 to, file a responsive pleading within 21 days. The court may grant a contin-
11 uance for good cause related to lack of or insufficiency of a responsive
12 pleading.”.
13 On page 6, line 7, delete “(2)” and insert “(3)”.
14 After line 18, insert:
15 “(3) Subsection (1) of this section does not apply to contempt proceedings
16 subject to ORS 107.728.”.
17 Delete lines 19 through 21 and insert:
18
19 “PARENTAGE PROCEEDINGS
20
21 “SECTION 7. ORS 109.232 is amended to read:

1 “109.232. (1) [A petition and any other document related to a surrogacy
2 agreement filed with the court shall be sealed,] A case for determination
3 of parentage of a child born by assisted reproduction under a
4 gestational surrogacy agreement shall be confidential, exempt from
5 public disclosure under ORS 192.311 to 192.478 and may not be disclosed ex-
6 cept:
7 “(a) To a party to the proceeding;
8 “(b) To a child conceived by assisted reproduction under the agreement;
9 “(c) To an attorney of a party to the proceeding or a child conceived by
10 assisted reproduction under the agreement;
11 “(d) The court; or
12 “(e) Pursuant to a court order for good cause shown, and subject to the
13 provisions of ORS 192.324.
14 “[(2) The individual seeking to inspect the document may be required to pay
15 the expense of preparing a copy of the document to be inspected.]
16 “(2) If an individual authorized to access the case seeks copies of
17 case documents, the court may require the individual to pay the ex-
18 pense of preparing copies of the documents.
19 “SECTION 8. Upon the motion of a party to a case described in ORS
20 109.232 that was initiated before September 29, 2025, the court shall
21 make the case confidential and subject to the confidentiality pro-
22 visions prescribed in ORS 109.232.
23
24 “APPLICABILITY
25
26 “SECTION 9. Section 6 of this 2026 Act and the amendments to ORS
27 33.055, 33.065, 33.075 and 476.274 by sections 1 to 4 of this 2026 Act apply
28 to contempt proceedings initiated on or after January 1, 2027.
29 “SECTION 10. The amendments to ORS 109.232 by section 7 of this
30 2026 Act apply to cases initiated on or after September 29, 2025, and,
